        <p>Despite disagreements, most experts agree on several points:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Insulin resistance and metabolic dysfunction are major cardiovascular risk factors</li>
            <li>Ultra-processed foods are harmful</li>
            <li>Lifestyle factors (diet, exercise, sleep, stress) powerfully affect heart disease risk</li>
            <li>Standard risk calculators have significant limitations</li>
            <li>Women and minorities have been underserved by cardiovascular research</li>
            <li>Inflammation plays a central role in atherosclerosis</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

